SIMPLE: remembrance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remembrance
<hw>Re*mem"brance</hw> <pr>(-br<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>remembrance</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of remembering; a holding in mind, or
bringing to mind; recollection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest fierce <qex>remembrance</qex> wake my sudden rage.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest the <qex>remembrance</qex> of his grief should fail.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being remembered, or held in mind;
memory; recollection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This, ever grateful, in <qex>remembrance</qex> bear.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something remembered; a person or thing kept in
memory.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>That which serves to keep in or bring to mind; a
memorial; a token; a memento; a souvenir; a memorandum or note of
something to be remembered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And on his breast a bloody cross he bore,⟦br⟧
The dear <qex>remembrance</qex> of his dying Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Keep this <qex>remembrance</qex> for thy Julia's sake.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Something to be remembered; counsel; admonition;
instruction.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Power of remembering; reach of personal knowledge;
period over which one's memory extends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thee I have heard relating what was done⟦br⟧
Ere my <qex>remembrance</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Recollection; reminiscence. See
<er>Memory</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remembrancer</ent>⟦br⟧
